opening_comment: The Three Corners Happy Life Marsa Alam, Egypt Marsa `Alam, Al Bahr Al Ahmar, Egypt A 4 stars all-inclusive beach resort featuring 300 rooms, 2 swimmings pool, a lazy river and an aquapark  Located on the west coast of the Red Sea 25 km south of Marsa Alam International Airport, The Three Corners Happy Life Resort is a true paradise holiday seekers, windsurfers, scuba divers, snorkelers and sun-worshipers alike.  The 4 stars all-inclusive beach resort features 300 rooms spread over a main building and several low-rise buildings, 2 swimmings pool, a children pool, a lazy river and 3 water slides. The mini club and a playground await the younger ones.  The main building features the reception and a lobby, the main restaurant and one of the three available bars. Both on the 800 meters beach front and by the large sundecks at the pools Sun beds and umbrellas as well as the towel service can be used free of charge. The Three Corners Happy Life Resort offers a multitude of facilities with an emphasis on sports, alongside relaxation and recreation.  For active vacationers, the resort offers swimming pools, scuba diving facilities, diversified water activities, and organized beach sports events. For those who opt for a good treat while on holiday, a highly equipped fitness and beauty center will take care of your needs. The wonderful house-reef and the swimming area can easily be reached through our jetty that enters the sea for about 100 meters.  Our professional and multilingual animation team promises a lot of fun and enjoyment.

opening_comment: The Temple of Philae, a symbol of ancient Egyptian ingenuity, sits majestically on Philae Island in the Nile River, drawing visitors with its intricate architecture and spiritual significance. Dedicated primarily to the goddess Isis, this temple complex boasts a rich history dating back to the 4th century BCE, showcasing a blend of Egyptian, Greek, and Roman influences. Its relocation to Agilkia Island in the 1960s preserved its grandeur amidst threats of submersion due to the Aswan High Dam. Philae Temple's architectural marvels include the awe-inspiring Hypostyle Hall, adorned with towering columns and elaborate hieroglyphs, and sacred sanctuaries steeped in mythological reliefs. Egypt Tours Plus website( https://www.egypttoursplus.com/ ) offers an unparalleled opportunity to explore Philae Temple and other Egyptian wonders, with expert guides and customizable itineraries ensuring an immersive journey through ancient history. Embark on a voyage of discovery with Egypt Tours Plus, uncovering the secrets of the pharaohs as you cruise down the Nile or explore hidden archaeological gems in the desert. Philae Temple stands as a timeless testament to Egypt's rich heritage, inviting travelers to experience its splendor and spirituality firsthand.

opening_comment: When I was a young boy, we would travel every spring and every summer to the northern coast of the Mediterranean. After a four hour drive on the desert road, we would pass through the unofficial gates of Alexandria, turn off the rickety air conditioning, and swiftly roll down our windows. After hours packed between my siblings and the dead silence of my parents, we would all look to our left, stick our arms outside the windows and imitate the rolling movement of the sea’s waves in sync. Together, we would breathe in the salty wind before we made our way down the corniche to my grandfather’s house. To us, the sea was a marker of our arrival, an emblem of our hometown, and a symbol of a long-sought peace of mind. Although the Mediterranean acts as a border in Alexandria, it seemed to us as an extension of the city.
